http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Mangalore/Konkan-Railway-train-schedule-to-be-changed-for-10-days/article14022761.ece

Train services on the Konkan Railway network to and from Kerala would be affected for 12 days — from January 30 to February 10 — due to work on removal of scissor crossovers at Ernakulam junction, Konkan Railway Corporation said.The Madgaon Express will be partially cancelled between Aluva and Ernakulam on February 1, while several trains would be diverted via Kottayam, Ernakulam Town and Chengannur, the Corporation said in a release.List of diverted trains:1. Kochuveli-Chandigarh Express leaving Kochuveli on Jan 30, Feb 1, 6 and 8;2. Thiruvananthapuram-Lokamanya Tilak Terminal Express leaving Thiruvananthapuram on Jan 30 and Feb 10;3. Tirunelveli-Hapa Express leaving Tirunelveli on Feb 8;4. Kochuveli-Amritsar Express leaving Kochuveli on Feb 3 and 10;5. Porbandar-Kochuveli Express leaving Porbandar on Jan 28 and Feb 4;6. Amritsar-Kochuveli Express leaving Amritsar on Jan 31 and Feb 7.